reviews_data.review_text: So good!! The muffins are the best!
I missed the previous owners, the place doesn't feel cozy anymore, it looks empty, the bakery shelf's barely have any pastries, they don't do cakes  and is just not the same.
Stake items unpleasant owner

So my boyfriend came here 6 years ago and every time we pass through the area he tells me how amazing it is. Well we finally were able to stop today and I have to say his hype was fully justified. We both had a handmade, fresh cannoli. He had a large vanilla latte and I had an iced latte with almond milk, honey, and cinnamon. The food and drinks were absolutely amazing. Definitely stop in!!
The previous owners were better and it seems that the store is closed alot.
The people here are amazing and the food/beverages are wonderful! The owner is always kind and the place is so cute inside!

Went the park with the grandkids and stopped here.  Love that they carry Waxhaw Creamy Ice cream.  The kids enjoyed the cotton candy and black raspberry ice cream while I cooled off with an Ice Caramel Coffee
Cute cafe! Great vibes and the man at the register was very nice l! Also chicken salad was bomb

My buddy and I stopped at the location. It was early in the morning and stop for coffee and something to drink. My buddy got the strawberry smoothie and I got one of the specialty coffees and a muffin. My friend said the strawberry smoothie had good sweetness and strawberry flavor. As for me, I think I got the cloud nine espresso drink. It was Good balance of sweetness and coffee flavor with the right amount of foam. The our only thing was it was a little cooler than I like for a hot drink but didn't deter. Now the muffins were wonderful, I got a cinnamon muffin and a chocolate chip muffins. Both had wonderful flavor both, the cinnamon had a good balance of sweetness and  cinnamon flavor. The chocolate chip muffin had just the right amount of chocolate chips to muffin ratio. Both were really moist with a perfect outer crust. I would highly recommend this place for coffee and muffins. The gentleman behind the counter was nice and polite and efficient.

I used to love stopping in to take a meeting but now the location is filled with kids things and out of date decor. It's a little sad but the muffins were awesome and the coffee is good so you can't win 'em all. Not very inviting. No music. Not very clean. Needs an overhaul.

Went for late lunch and they were out of eggs, croissant, no longer carry chicken salad. Had a plain bagel with cream cheese - disappointed especially since I drove from Burlington NC to stop here.  Clerk very nice & apologetic.

Was here this morning. Expecting to enjoy coffee and pastries with a friend. No-one was at the counter. Rang the bell a few times. Nope. No-one showed up. There were a handful of people sitting there, just chatting. Didn't really noticed if they had anything on their tables. Finally we decided to leave. Very disappointed.

We came for coffee and breakfast. The food was delicious and there was a small play area for my kids to play while I got to enjoy my food and coffee peacefully. Great small local coffee shop. Highly recommend!
Coffee was good and the lemon bar were very enjoyable. There wasn't a very wide selection of baked goods but maybe that is dependent on time(I arrived around noon).
We love going here and getting a pastry or something for lunch. We aren't coffee drinkers so can't speak to that but the pastries are delicious and we enjoy the Mexican coke and smoothies.

The coffee was good however the place is honestly gross. The bathrooms were not clean, floors are dirty walls are dirty just not clean in general. I won't be back for this reason, sadly even though the coffee was good.
I've had better!
Was visiting my friend and we stopped by for coffee. Had their muffins and it was delicious. Will definitely stop by here again for breakfast.

The new older is extremely nice, friendly and much better then the previous owner.  I am excited to see that changes he has made and the food is fresh and delicious.  Had their new chicken salad sandwich and a coffee and it was great!

They also now carry Waxhaw creamery ice cream. I don't have to go downtown waxhaw to get their ice cream
Had bacon egg and cheese sandwich. It's nice size. The place is clean and comfortable. One employee nice friendly knowledgeable man. I'm sure we will return.

A really cute coffee shop with the best staff! They have so many flavors to choose from, personally love the iced coffee with salted caramel and oatmilk. The Croissants are also incredibly light and savory.
If you are in need of a coffee you MUST try their **Cloud 9**. It is absolutely amazing. My kids enjoy their treats (too many to to name) and ice cream.

Such an amazing and friendly staff there! William Bonilla has turned Java into a cool modern coffee shop. And not to mention the coffee is so good and made fresh ! Side note : icecream in a coffee shop = best decision ever
Nice little place

The coffee is really good but the breakfast sandwiches are the BEST! Bacon egg and cheese on an everything bagel was SO good!!!! Probably one of the best I've had in the area. The pastries were also great -- we tried a variety and all amazing! The owner is a really nice guy!!
Staff is always pleasant and great prices
Excellent eclair and Latte, it was a perfect afternoon pick-me-up!
Great coffee, food, and atmosphere!  Lots of space to sit and get some work done or read a book.
Spent $20 on 3 confections to share at home.  All 3 were disappointing.  Wish I had my $ back to spend at a different sweet shop or bakery.

We have regulars here for lunch for a few years.  It was sold a while back and we had a bad experience.  We waited a few weeks and thought we should give it another chance just to be fair.  They have a big sign over the counter with menu and prices.  You can build your own sandwich for $10.50.  It lists the different sandwich items and breads, one of which is a croissant.  The price we were charged was $10.87 per sandwich plus $2.33 each for the croissants.  They no longer bake every day so the croissants were not fresh.  They also had no diet soft drinks of any kind.  Since the old owners left it has gone down considerably.  When I asked about the differences in the prices and the additional cost for the croissants I was told that is the way they do it now.  No apology of any kind.  I have never written a business a bad review of any kind so this cannot be written of to me just being a complainer.  I am just the opposite.  We will not be back.
Great little coffee shop in the Weddington area
I'm not a regular coffee drinker, but the Cloud 9 was good. The croissant was fluffy and goes perfect with your added ingredients at home.  The service was excellent.

We stopped by at 9:30am. There were no other customers and only few selections of pastries. Ordered 3 plain bagels and one croissant and that was $21 with change. Said: no thank you I am definitely not paying $21 for one pastry and 3 bagels.  Price is outrageous.
Best cappuccino I've had since I left Connecticut!
The coffee is always perfect. Regardless of whether Joyce, Zev, or Sherry make it.

Best kept secret. Maybe not a secret anymore? The homemade baked goods are bar none. I love their croissant breakfast sandwiches (baked in house) and they make the best Chai latte I've ever had. It's not a pre-packaged syrup/mix. My husband loves the Mocha Diablo latte. Great corner seating in cozy chairs with lamp lighting or table options. Also has a play kitchen for the kids.
Good coffee. Lots of cute things to buy and delicious pastries.
Nice little coffee shop with yummy looking Desserts. Had a great frozen mocha drink with peppermint flavor added.
Cakes are fresh and soft delicious

My husband and I visited recently and got some pastries. I'm very picky about my pastries. Everything was amazing! The chocolates are rich, I could taste the milk in the creme of the eclairs, and they were sweet but not too sweet. Also, this place just has a vibe about it. One that makes you feel like you're at a Thanksgiving gathering with family.
Lots of great pastries.
Such a sweet spot! Coffee is wonderful as is the food. Staff is very kind as well

The coffee is much better than Starbucks and my favorite is Salted Caramel Latte. Enjoy delicious home-made muffins and sweet snacks, like the French Toast Muffins and my favorite sandwich is lox with toasted bagel, with all the fixins.' You can't go wrong at this little shop!

Absolutely incredible coffee shop and bakery. The owner Zev is incredibly kind and the work he and his wife do to put out the impeccable pastries, cookies, pies and other baked goods is unmatched. We adore their shop and highly recommend stopping in to get yourself a whirlwind of delicious and beautiful handmade baked goods!!!
This place is a gem! Pastries are beautiful made. Great friendly service and atmosphere
they make best Napoleon. highly recommended
We have visited here years ago but have not been since as we do not live local.  We decided to stop in and pick up some dessert.  Everything was delicious!  Look forward to returning.
Cafe was closed, but still the gentleman came out and offered to make us the drink. Friendly staff
Best Bakery in town! Please stop by and take advantage of everything this place has to offer, you won't be disappointed!
Highly recommended.  Some of the best coffees I've ever had.

Great fresh selection of pastries and sandwiches. They even have their own, unique blend of coffee beans, choose your favorite. Very welcoming family owned business, support local business, they need it during these crazy times and it's well deserved! Zev is a great host! 5

I came in because my internet at home has not been working well and needed somewhere close to home to work and headed here because they are close by. I don't really drink coffee much but everything looked fantastic as far as coffee. I got a sandwich called The Eastern Europe on an everything bagel. The bagel was phenomenal. Also the sandwich was as well. The atmosphere was great abd had a very local vibe. I will be back. Maybe try the coffee or gelato next time.

4.5
Pequena cafeteria con variedad de pasteles y bebidas originales  tanto calientes como frias. El hombre que nos atendio fue super agradable nos asesoro, recomendo y adapto las bebidas a nuestro gusto.
Tienen un area para que los ninos jueguen y se distraigan.
El establecimiento y mobiliario parece estar un poco deteriorado.

I've always wondered about this place because I drive past it all the time. Finally decided to come in get a little work done and enjoy my coffee. So glad I came in, very friendly staff. Adorable environment. Lots of little spaces that you can just sit and do your thing. I will definitely be back. Also love the cappuccino and although I didn't partake in any of the pastries, let me say they look amazing!
Pretty good environment and coffee
This place was awesome. The coffee was unbelievable and the pastries were delicious. We don't live in the area, but I have a feeling we're going to" swing by" here a lot more often now.
Beautiful place for coffee lovers. Morning relaxing. Great croissants my co worker eats here every morning I'm going back for soap and cheese cake  smoothies lovers u should try here
Amazing cup of coffee had the Cloud 9!!!

My fiance and I went here to try bakeries for our upcoming wedding, we were both blown away. The service was excellent and the baked goods were by far the best I've ever tasted. We are both very picky about cakes and flavors, no complaints from us at all. We felt to important when we left, like our presence matter to Java. We will definitely be coming back here soon.  All our love to the owners, you're doing amazing!
Absolutely love this place! The people are super nice and all the food and desserts are delicious. Totally recommend:)

The Grinch May Have Stolen Christmas but he sure was super moist and flavorful from Java's Brewing Bakery. No seriously! This cake was a hit at our Ugly Sweater gathering and our guests are still singing the baker's praise. As every baker knows, its hard to find a cake that looks good and taste good - usually one suffers for the other however not my Grinch cake - It looked and tasted yummy! Its was perfectly topped with the right amount of frosting and accomodated all my 25 guests with leftovers for the following week. The service here is suberb! They go above and beyond to meet your request and end products speaks for itself.
It was awesome.  They have the best hot chocolate. The waiter was very friendly and nice. I would differently go back.
Lots of variety of fresh pastries and delicious drinks. Cloud 9 was delicious and the barista was super friendly. Will be back to try more soon

Always a good assortment of bakery items. Gluten free coconut macaroons are a favorite for me as well as GF creme brulee. Variety of muffins from regular chocolate chip type flavors to french toast and Oreo muffins. Love the fact that it is family owned and operated. Sometimes that means a longer wait, but worth it to support local.
Amazing place. Great baked goods,  nice food. Lovely owners.

Java's Brewing Bakery and Cafe is incredible! I ordered a cake for my Son's College Graduation celebration. Joyce was so helpful in recommending different cake options. Her expertise is obvious the minute you first speak with her. The finished product looked great and was absolutely delicious.
The cake itself was so fresh, it beats any store bought cake for sure!
Joyce went above and beyond by doing me a huge favor & delivering the cake to the restaurant. Talk about customer service! I cannot say enough good things about Zev & Joyce.
Cakes are amazing.
Great coffee cake muffin and dark roast.
Great little coffee shop, the batista was very attentive and friendly.
Visit here every trip to waxhaw. Great coffee and muffins.
Amazing! Great pastries! Amazing staff! 10/10

Incredible place! Been looking since I moved here for my regular bakery, and this is my new go-to spot. Friendly and casual and the best selection I've found. Most of the places I've tried have tarts only, or a few muffins only, etc, but they have anything you could want that comes out an oven and can be eaten for breakfast or an afternoon treat. I'll be back! Pumpkin muffin whips Panera's by a mile.
Great experience. Cute shop staff was helpful and nice. Iced mocha with almond milk was delicious.
The service is amazing

Los pastelitos estan delicioso con la diferencia que unos son demasiado dulce de arriba, pero el renedo del pan esta delicioso.
El lugar es muy decorativo y limpio.
The pastries were delicious. With the difference being that the icing on the cake where way too sweet while the filling inside the cake was delish.
The place is very decorative and clean
This is such a cute Cafe! And the staff is friendly. Also they really will customize your coffee, I don't find many places that makes coffee the way I really like. But they did!
Great lattes and sandwiches! One of the best croissants my daughter has ever had, and she gets them at every coffee shop. The owner is always friendly too!
The Best pastries and desserts, with coffee to the max!
Friendly staff with a wide variety of food and drinks.
Great food and service. I will be sure to stop by again when in the area.
Didn't say that their place was closed on Google map. It was a big waste of time coming out here.
The owner is so kind and generous. The coffee and pastries are very good
To the lady behind the counter today who made me an amazing Cloud 9 -- you were pleasant and friendly, Java is lucky to have you! My Cloud 9 tastes delicious. Can't wait to visit again!
Good food but breakfast cost me $17 for a sandwich and coffee.

YOUR PHONE NUMBER IS COMPROMISED. I'm in Colorado and keep receiving spam calls from your number. The new tactic is to bounce calls through legitimate businesses so we can't differentiate between spam and real calls.

I know it isn't 'you' doing this and I am commenting to make you aware in case there are any actions you might be able to take to protect your businesses reputation.

I love coffee. So you get 5 stars too.
One of the nicest places to go for a cup of coffee and have a Danish everything in there is so nice and the people who work there are even nicer

Great place! Good good with some fairly unique sandwich selections. Two employees were incredibly helpful and friendly, and really wanted it experience to be good. Very clean and felt safe, and they had a way bigger selection of baked goods ready to go than I would have expected. Comfortable and great local coffee shop vibe, without being pretentious.

Delicious muffins but atmosphere needs a revamp if this place is going to survive long term with all the new building around the area. Modernise the seating and declutter and I think they would get alot more people through.
Great coffee .
Owner is one of a kind, kind. The place is comfortable and smoothies are amazing.

This place is amazing! Favorite coffee drink: Cloud 9. Favorite snack: Cannoli- hands down!

This isn't just a coffee shop. This is a little store with tons of cool little gifts, a place to meet up with friends for a brunch, a bakery, and I bet if you wanted you could even get lost in a book here.

I never leave disappointed.
The experience is something you have to try for yourself. I hope that it's as satisfying for you just how it's been for me.
Great pastries

Gotta give a shout out to this place that I stumbled across while stuck in traffic.  I never thought I could get gelato like I had in Italy but OMG I found it here!  Not only that, but the other baked goods are to die for too.  So glad this newcomer - me - discovered this place!! So good.  I'll be back!!

This place is the best! The owner is so kind. She remembers my order every time I come in, if that says anything ab how much I love this place. The cafe is super clean. She follows by the mask mandate, making all of her customers feel safe. Stop by sometime & Support local.
Great service. Delicious coffee and treats.

I can't reciew their food (because I was prevented from doing so) but I can review their service. They discriminate against people who can not wear face masks. They have 0% customer service, she did not even greet me and gave me a impatient look before she kicked me out. Love supporting local but I won't support anyone that doesn't respect me or my rights. You are breaking the law!
I love the Cloud 9 less sweet and egg & cheese on a toasted croissant.
Love all the cakes and pastries. I go here for every birthday cake.
Great place, but got dragged thru the coals, on a custom cake? owners are great people and  place is great and cozy and clean.
Had order their pie for Thanksgiving.  One of the best I've had in years.

I adore this place. It's cozy inside, the owners are delightful and everything is fantastic. I had the turkey, cranberry, walnut sandwich on a croissant...it was gone so fast I didn't snag a pic. I did however capture this beauty of a Napoleon before diving in. Check this place out, I promise you won't be disappointed!
Coffee in my opinion is expensive in compare with the service you get there.
I love love love this company and their work! They made my wedding cake and it was beautiful and delicious! Received tons of compliments on it! Would absolutely use them again!!!!!

Excellent food and excellent owners!
I could eat there seriously everyday!

Today is my first visit and I felt blessed by a kind gentleman who offered to pay for my cakes. The cakes are delicious and the kind gesture warmed my sunken  heart after so many months of hardship that I have gone through - my husband's cancer battle and the financial struggle that came with it. I don't know who you are, but I will pay it forward someday when I am able to. Thank you!
Lovely coffee shop and bakery.
She was so nice. Great place
The owner is very kind and likes to get to know his customers!
Good folks. Good service.
Loved its Tuna and spinach cheese bistro sandwich.
Cutest little coffee shop!!! Great desserts and tasty muffins.. coffee is wonderful! ( try a cloud 9 ;)) would highly recommend .
Theh make the best Napolean I've ever had!
Love this coffee shop! So relaxing and great product. Staff is super friendly.  Small area for young kids to play. The best pastries. I mean, who doesn't love cheesecake on a stick!?

This place is more than a superb coffee shop and bakery, it is an experience. A unique place with delicious pastries, novel coffee drinks and other items for purchase. Put this place on your list to visit.
Porque esta rriquisimo todos sus postresFruit cream puff
Great as always.
Friendly. Professional. Accommodating. Affordable. Delicious.
Got a couple desserts, they were good. The counters, and in general the whole place feels sticky. Could use a thorough clean.
Great service and another.. coffee is so so good.. Yummy

If you haven't been to Java's, you don't know what you're missing. They not only have great coffee, pastries, and food, but the entire environment is very inviting and a wonderful place to sit down and relax. The owners and staff are amazing people and very hospitable.
Best coffee around and amazing treats
Amazing service! I've been several times and have a great experience every time.
Fabulous cakes and ownership.
If you could bottle the smells!  Amazing...coffee, and baked good in the oven!  Everything is delicious...
Loved the light roast. The croisant was light and buttery tasty.

I've been blessed with the opportunity to live overseas and have visited several countries.  Java's has the best chai tea in the WORLD.  Zev is super friendly.  The ambiance of the cafe is terrific.  A sublime experience.
Yummy pumpkin spice muffin and friendly service
I really enjoyed stopping in after a weekend bike ride. The selection was a surprise but too irresistible.
Best deserts in Weddington area!!!! Awesome coffee as well
Wonderful coffee shop and bakery.  I had a  mocha coffee and a rasberry cheese strudel.  Both were excellent!

This bakery was recommended to me by several people. I ordered a birthday cake with cookies and cream filling and chocolate cake as my husband is an Oreo lover. This cake was phenomenal. The filling is spot on and not too sweet, just perfect. The cake altogether was absolutely delicious. Their 6 inch round was about 50 bucks but you actually get a lot of cake for that. Staff was so so friendly and super helpful (phone and counter). Only suggestion is to have more staff on hand on Saturdays. We picked up at noon on a Saturday and there seemed to only be one person working at the counter. She was lovely but it took a while to pick up. Will definitely be back and recommend to others!
This is a gem of a place! Friendly atmosphere, very personable staff, and excellent food. The fresh-baked goods are amazing and the coffee is flavorful. I'll be going back.
A must go to special coffee shop. Zev (the owner) is very friendly and accommodating. On top of that, he makes great coffee and excellent desserts. Check it out and you won't be disappointed.

The most underrated place in waxhaw unfortunately.
The atmosphere is very homely and welcoming, but it can also look a bit gloomy inside because of the dark colors used in the furniture, paint, etc.
In terms of the menu, there are a varietyy of options to choose from, ranging from coffees, snacks, breakfast and lunch items, cakes, pastries, cookies, gelato, and more! Prices are reasonable. When compared to Starbucks, this place is more worth it.
The customer service is good. Only thing though is that it is slow because there are usually only 2 people working at the front at a time.
Side note: please try the lox bagel ! ( only place I've been to so far with this on the menu)

Great "Local" Spot for desserts/drinks!

Zev has become what I would consider a good friend, & is always a friendly face.

Try the Apricot Dessert...Hard to find Apricot anything & this one is really delicious!
Great variety
The cake was really good
Friendly people and delicious cannoli
We got a iced mocha coffee, peach mango smoothie and a key lime pie! It was all wonderful
Awesome service, delicious desserts, warm, friendly atmosphere. Our whole family loves this place!  You must try the Napoleon!
Good iced mocha! Friendly staff and location isn't bad

I absolutely love coming to this place. The gentleman who runs it as always so nice and so friendly. I love coming here with friends and to read. This is one of the best coffee shops I've ever been to. It's a hidden gem. There is usually poplar music playing but it's never too loud. There are also so many wonderful drinks to choose from and several yummy desserts. I have never really run into a busy time & have always enjoyed going to sit in the same spot with my tea and a good book.
Great coffee and desserts... I definitely recommend.
Delicious as always. Baked goods are super fresh and baked in house.
Amazing pastries. Very nice owner. Would definitely recommend it.
Awesome people that feed me vanilla chai everyday and snowball cookies
Owner was extremely nice and coffee/pastries were delicious!
Always awesome....nothing better anywhere in this area
People are awesome, pastries are to die for
Great pasteries and friendly staff.  Highly recommend.
Friendly staff,good coffee !!!!!!!
Highly recommend! Zev is very welcoming and knowledgeable about his products. Great local spot!
Love it! Staff wonderful and coffee fresh!
Really good food
Awesome place and staff
A bit too pricey. Facility could use some sprucing up.
Great
A coffee place with great atmosphere and amazing pastries, one of the few with character left in the area.

A charming, peaceful nook that makes the best mochas and croissant breakfast sandwiches. Way more to offer here too but that's our favorites. Must dine in! In order to truly appreciate the atmosphere you have to take a seat, even if it's for a few minutes to relax.
Best pastries, great food, wonderful family business. Home made gelato and everything is made with love in the kitchen by the owners. Custom cakes for any occasions as well as wedding cakes!
Owner is super friendly. Great baked treats.
Best croissants in Charlotte!! Great and cozy place, amazing selection of pastries!! I'll definitely be back!
Great customer service!!
Best coffee and top notch pastries
Favorite waxhaw stop
Great iced coffee. The owner Zev really knows his product.
Good coffee. Really cute shop.
Very cute place, could use some more staffing. But I'm sure it will happen.
Great product!  Very friendly and helpful staff!  Nice welcoming and relaxing place.
Delicious toasted "everything" bagel with cream cheese. Opens early.  Coffee was excellent as well. Friendly place.
Amazing customer service & equally awesome desserts! Strawberry shortcake a must try.
Nice place with friendly staff and yummy food options including bakery goods. Definitely planning to lunch there again!
Great people and love the coffee selection.
Great little coffee shop on Providence and Newtown Roads.  Servers a great.  Plenty of seating inside and out.  Delicious breakfast treats as well.
Great variety of specialty baked goods

A true hidden gem! The name is misleading because while the coffee is good, the bakery is fantastic! Think perfect almond cherry tarts, french macaroons, scones, etc all from scratch using fresh butter, cream, and high quality ingredients . This is the kind of bakery you read about in books.
Excellent pastries, great coffee!

Owners - Joyce and Zev, along with Barista - Cheri - ALWAYS make John, my husband, and I feel like Family, with the Best Coffee and Most Delicious Pastry, Cakes, and Food around!!  We Love Them!!!  Thank You for what Y'all provide All of Us in Your Warm & Cozy Place, while we Enjoy it!!!
Good but expensive.
Awesome experience and great quality pastries and coffee! I love the atmosphere in there and the conolis are my absolute favorite!
Good lattes and great baked goods. Will return!
Helpful, nice,  offer breakfast all day!   Will be back again!
Love this place.
Always a grest place for coffee or baked goods

I love Java's! The chai latte tea here is my favorite! They also make amazing treats that you have to go see and try.
If you want to sit and enjoy your cup of joe there are multiple comfy couches and chairs, maybe even get some work done on your laptop since they also have WiFi available.
Once you visit once, you'll be sure to keep coming back!
Cozy place to meet for coffee.

Love this place been coming here for over a year now. Very friendly and great desserts. The chicken salad sandwich is to die for. Love cinnamon try their cloud 9 it's fantastic. Great place to relax and have a bite after dropping the kids off to school .
A little pricey and not a very large selection however  what they had was delicious.

The owner is always incredibly friendly when we visit. We're there in the evenings so I'm not sure how crowded it is during the usual coffee rush. The pastries and cakes are always fresh and our son loves visiting when we're next door for karate lessons.
Food and coffee is great. The apple turnovers are fantastic. Great place to sit and chat.  They even have an area for small gifts and an area for children to play so moms could relax
Amazing coffee, amazing pastries.  Owner was extremely nice- and knowledgeable passionate about baking and coffee! Awesome!!!
Good coffee. I felt the pastries were ok but not fresh.
Try the mocha diablo and tell him Gina sent you!
Best bagel I've ever had. Authentic, independent, great food and atmosphere.
Just okay on quality, but the service is great
Cute place with a great vibe.  The people are so nice and the sweet treats look amazing!

Cool little place in a convenient location.  I like that there are toys for kids to play with - which means that I can meet a friend for coffee for an hour without having to entertain my son while we catch up. Service is sometimes a bit slow, but the people are really nice.  I haven't had any of the cakes or baked goods, but they look fantastic!
A bit pricey and tricky to get in and out when traffic is heavy on route 16, but I've stopped a couple times now. Cappuccinos were very good, pastries were delicious, and service was friendly.
The finest Napoleon within 50 miles of Charlotte.  As good as any you'd find in NY, NJ, or Boston.  Many other equally excellent pastries and baked goods, including beautiful Croissants.

I've been to hundreds of coffee shops, and in two visits to Java's Brewing and Bakery and Cafe', this might be the worst. Unfortunately, the barista Joyce is simply unfriendly and seems extremely unhappy. The signage in the shop makes it feel like the grinch himself is the owner (a couple attached in review). I've never paid more for a simple doppio (double espresso). With a random $.40 charge for a purchase under $5, my doppio cost $3.55 before tip, and this is Waxhaw, NC. Joyce seemed very disappointed that this was all I wanted and nearly pleaded for me to buy some pastries in an upsell attempt. I don't see myself coming back except out of some unforeseen necessity.
Best sweets in NC

Best independent coffee shop in the area, great service! (They even have a toy-kitchen set for the kiddies to play with while you enjoy your coffee) Good coffee and all of their cakes and pastries are made on-site.
Awesome place. Reccommended: mango smoothie.
Delious!! Smoothies are good!!

Let me start with the positive - - Their baked goods are great. Great tasting, and generously sized. Their coffee drinks are decent. Location is very convenient. Fantastic hours.

Now the negatives.. Overall unfriendly vibe.  I'm not saying the employees are rude, but for the most part they are typically not very friendly and seem inconvenienced by waiting on you to make a decision, even if you just walked in the door. Not to mention the off putting signs everywhere. "Bathrooms for customers only". Seriously? You're located in a tiny shopping center with a bank and a dance studio, how much foot traffic could you possibly be getting that is going to use your toilet and not buy something?? Just seems tacky and cheap.

My biggest stink is their 40 Cent transaction fee for purchases under 5 dollars. I am familiar with merchant fees charged my Visa, MC, Amex & Discover. Even on a 5 dollar purchase at a merchant charge of 5% of the purchase only comes out to .25 cents (15 Cent surplus). So they are blindly charging a random number and profiting on the rest.(Fees are much closer to 2% and 3%). 3% on 5 dollars is 15 cents. That is a 25 cent profit on every transaction under 5 dollars. A purchase under $5 is pretty easy to do if you just want a coffee or a muffin. Now am I really bothered by a 40 cent charge added to my 5 dollar coffee? No, not really. But the principle of this is wrong. Charging your customers an additional fee for trying to pay? That screams "struggling business". It's the 21st century, Many people don't pay with cash, as paying with a bank card is far more convenient. If you want the business, bite the bullet and pay the transaction fee.

My advice? If a business is in the red over a matter of 40 cents and having people use their water by flushing their toilets, they probably shouldn't be in business.
Loved everything we tried here from the coffee to the muffins and breakfast sandwich in between. :)

First off props for being one of the only coffee shops open till 9 pm!  That alone makes this place good in my book.

The place
It is located in a little shopping center you can see it from the road. Inside they have a nice coffee shop feel.  They have a TV and even toys for kids to play so if you decide to go for coffee and want to bring your kids. They have some really cool mugs for sale to check out while you are the there.

The coffee

I ordered the Iced Almond Roca latte which was very good.  It had great flavor with a good balance of sweet yet able to taste the coffee. They also have a nice selection of desserts. I trusted the guy and went with a the Turtle brownie and my wife had the lemon butter tart. Both had great flavor were good choices.  If you are looking for a great non Starbucks coffee shop that you can bring your kids and has great hours you need to check this place out!

I have been nothing but pleased with my experiences at Java's Brewing!  Their customer service is great as I can walk in and ask for my "usual" and they know just what to whip up!  I have so enjoyed their muffins that this morning I decided to pick up a dozen to take to work for my co-workers and they were gone before I knew it.  I actually drive the longer route to work so I can stop at Java's on the way to work, as I was unable to find a bakery that even compared on the shorter way to work (keep in mind it takes me 45min to an hour to get to work)!
